item.title: Madison College Performing Arts Presents Grapes of Wrath
item.description:
Truax-Main Building - Rm A1017 Mitby Theater
Friday, November 4, 2016, 7:30 – 10pm
Madison College Performing Arts presents Grapes of Wrath by John Steinbeck, adapted for the stage by Frank Galati.
For tickets
Set during the Great Depression, the play focuses on the Joads, a poor family of tenant farmers driven from their Oklahoma home by drought, economic hardship, agricultural industry changes and bank foreclosures forcing tenant farmers out of work. Due to their nearly hopeless situation, and in part because they are trapped in the Dust Bowl, the Joads set out for California. Along with thousands of other "Okies", they seek jobs, land, dignity, and a future. (Wikipedia)
Event Name: Grapes of Wrath
Event State: Confirmed
Organizer: MHawk@madisoncollege.edu
Expected Headcount: 250
Organization: Performing Arts
Categories: Featured Event, Truax, Event - Public Performances and Special Events
